			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Interactive Disambiguation of Meta Programs with Concrete Object Syntax</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LennartCLKats.html">Lennart C. L. Kats</a>, <a href="../profile/KarlTrygveKalleberg.html">Karl Trygve Kalleberg</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_22">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_22</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The paper concerns meta-programming over object languages with concrete syntax, i.e., metalanguage design/use.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> Interactive disambiguation is a tooling problem addressing how meta-programs are edited and resolved in practice.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> It touches language-design choices around integrating concrete syntax into meta-programming.
</li></ul></li></ul>
